            <div type="note">
                <head type="title"><persName corresp="#ALLENH">Hugh Allen</persName> (<!--Entry needed here.-->)</head>
                <p>Next eldest son, after his brother <persName corresp="#ALLENW">William</persName>, of <persName corresp="#GA">George Allen</persName>. In <date when="1901">1901</date>, along with
                    <persName corresp="#ALLENW">William</persName> and his sister <persName corresp="#ALLENG">Grace</persName>, he became a member of the board of the publishing
                    business now named <orgName corresp="#GEORGEALLEN">George Allen and Sons</orgName>. With <persName corresp="#ETC">E. T. Cook</persName>, he cataloged the
                    drawings for the bibliography volume (vol. 38) of the <title type="book" corresp="#JRWORKSLE">Library Edition</title>. <persName corresp="#ALLENH">Hugh</persName>
                    served as an agent for <!--Entry needed here.--> at the important <title type="catalog_aution" corresp="#SOTHEBYCAT1930">Sotheby&#x02BC;s sales of 1930</title>
                    and <date when="1931">1931</date> of <persName corresp="#JR">Ruskin</persName>&#x02BC;s remaining library and manuscripts.</p>
                <p>See <ref type="bibliography" target="bibliography.php#DAWSONPEOPLESRUSKIN"><persName corresp="#DAWSONP">Dawson</persName>, <title type="book" corresp="#DAWSONPEOPLESRUSKIN"><hi rend="italic">People&#x2019;s Ruskin</hi></title></ref>, 10;
                    <ref type="bibliography" target="bibliography.php#DEARDENLIBRARYEDITION"><persName corresp="#JSD">Dearden</persName>, <title type="book" corresp="#JRWORKSLE">&#x201C;Library Edition of the Works of John Ruskin&#x201D;,</title></ref>ref>
                    61.</p>
            </div>
